From: Chad Monroe <chad@monroe.io>
Date: Thu, 26 Feb 2026 12:40:43 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: fix STA CSA abort WARN_ON and stale auth blocking

ieee80211_sta_abort_chanswitch() unconditionally calls unreserve when a
chanctx_conf exists, but the OTHER_LINK CSA disappearance path can reach
abort with no reservation, hitting WARN_ON(!ctx). Guard the unreserve
call with a reserved_chanctx check.

After AP CSA completes, 1-2 beacons leak with stale CSA IEs due to
two-phase finalization. ieee80211_mgd_csa_present() only ignores
same-channel CSA when mode==0, but APs typically use mode==1, so STAs
caching these beacons are permanently blocked from authenticating. Drop
the mode check since the STA has not transmitted anything yet.

Signed-off-by: Chad Monroe <chad@monroe.io>
---
 net/mac80211/mlme.c |    7 ++++---
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/net/mac80211/mlme.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/mlme.c
@@ -2616,7 +2616,8 @@ ieee80211_sta_abort_chanswitch(struct ie
 	if (!local->ops->abort_channel_switch)
 		return;
 
-	if (rcu_access_pointer(link->conf->chanctx_conf))
+	if (rcu_access_pointer(link->conf->chanctx_conf) &&
+	    link->reserved_chanctx)
 		ieee80211_link_unreserve_chanctx(link);
 
 	ieee80211_vif_unblock_queues_csa(sdata);
@@ -9135,12 +9136,12 @@ static bool ieee80211_mgd_csa_present(st
 
 	if (csa && csa->count == 0)
 		csa = NULL;
-	if (csa && !csa->mode && csa->new_ch_num == cur_channel)
+	if (csa && csa->new_ch_num == cur_channel)
 		csa = NULL;
 
 	if (ecsa && ecsa->count == 0)
 		ecsa = NULL;
-	if (ecsa && !ecsa->mode && ecsa->new_ch_num == cur_channel)
+	if (ecsa && ecsa->new_ch_num == cur_channel)
 		ecsa = NULL;
 
 	if (ignore_ecsa && ecsa) {
